Position: Full-Time QA Tester - WFH/Remote (Fresh Graduates Welcome to Apply)
Job_Description:
Company Description

SEEKA Technologies (Not Seeka Limited) is a project under its parent organization called Fresh Futures Australia which is an education consultant based in both Australia and Malaysia. It will be a huge platform that utilises A.I. to help match students and job seekers to the right opportunities relevant to them from Primary/Grade school to University level as well as language schools and job opportunities. Our mission is to make it easier for anyone to find, filter and apply to different schools or educational institutions that suit them best as well as make the transition from studies to work more seamless.
We are seeking a detail-oriented QA Tester to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring that all of our software products meet the highest standards of quality and reliability. You will work closely with developers, product managers, and other team members to identify, report, and track bugs and issues. Your main goal will be to ensure that our software products are functional, user-friendly, and meet the needs of our clients.
Salary range will depend on your overall academic qualifications and experience post graduation and will be discussed with you should you be shortlisted for the job.

Job Description
Testing each and every button, page, feature and tool on our platform to verify the functionality and quality of our platform
To create and execute test plans, test cases, and test scripts
Using MS Excel or Google sheets to document each and every step you took to arrive at any results you find and the important things ti note about the result
Documenting any problems, issues and bugs you find that would severely affect the user experience
Using Adobe XD to open prototype designs and analyze the UI/UX
Communicate with team members and stakeholders to provide updates on testing progress and results

Qualifications
A Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology and any related field.
Proven experience as a QA Tester or similar role
Knowledge of software testing methodologies and best practices
Familiarity with bug tracking software
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Ability to work independently and as part of a team
Detail-oriented with a strong focus on quality

Additional Information
Completely remote or work from home (Very good if you also want to spend more time with family)
Friendly and understanding colleagues
You get to work in an agile work environment
You get to show your leadership skills
International working exposure
Company shares can be offered based on how successful with our products' launch
Company sponsored online classes or tech talks
Bonuses if you perform beyond expectation
Promotions towards better job roles possible after a certain period of time

About DigitalTolk
DigitalTolk is an organisation and company that works to make an impact. Our purpose is to give a voice to those who don’t speak the local language; we arrange translators so that patients can get medical treatments in their new country and communicate with doctors. We arrange translators for crime victims so that they can get justice. Our job is to arrange interpreters through our platform for our customers.
Our end customers are hospitals, courts/lawyers, and municipalities who communicate with refugees and other people in need.
Our company purpose is to use technology to make the world a better place. And we’re currently hiring developers to join us on this journey!
We are a company based in Sweden with developers in all parts of the planet!

Position: Full-Time QA Tester - WFH/Remote (Fresh Graduates Welcome to Apply)
Job_Description:
Company Description

SEEKA Technologies (Not Seeka Limited) is a project under its parent organization called Fresh Futures Australia which is an education consultant based in both Australia and Malaysia. It will be a huge platform that utilises A.I. to help match students and job seekers to the right opportunities relevant to them from Primary/Grade school to University level as well as language schools and job opportunities. Our mission is to make it easier for anyone to find, filter and apply to different schools or educational institutions that suit them best as well as make the transition from studies to work more seamless.
We are seeking a detail-oriented QA Tester to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring that all of our software products meet the highest standards of quality and reliability. You will work closely with developers, product managers, and other team members to identify, report, and track bugs and issues. Your main goal will be to ensure that our software products are functional, user-friendly, and meet the needs of our clients.
Salary range will depend on your overall academic qualifications and experience post graduation and will be discussed with you should you be shortlisted for the job.

Job Description
Testing each and every button, page, feature and tool on our platform to verify the functionality and quality of our platform
To create and execute test plans, test cases, and test scripts
Using MS Excel or Google sheets to document each and every step you took to arrive at any results you find and the important things ti note about the result
Documenting any problems, issues and bugs you find that would severely affect the user experience
Using Adobe XD to open prototype designs and analyze the UI/UX
Communicate with team members and stakeholders to provide updates on testing progress and results

Qualifications
A Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology and any related field.
Proven experience as a QA Tester or similar role
Knowledge of software testing methodologies and best practices
Familiarity with bug tracking software
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Ability to work independently and as part of a team
Detail-oriented with a strong focus on quality

Additional Information
Completely remote or work from home (Very good if you also want to spend more time with family)
Friendly and understanding colleagues
You get to work in an agile work environment
You get to show your leadership skills
International working exposure
Company shares can be offered based on how successful with our products' launch
Company sponsored online classes or tech talks
Bonuses if you perform beyond expectation
Promotions towards better job roles possible after a certain period of time

Position: Full-Time QA Tester - WFH/Remote (Fresh Graduates Welcome to Apply)
Job_Description:
Company Description

SEEKA Technologies (Not Seeka Limited) is a project under its parent organization called Fresh Futures Australia which is an education consultant based in both Australia and Malaysia. It will be a huge platform that utilises A.I. to help match students and job seekers to the right opportunities relevant to them from Primary/Grade school to University level as well as language schools and job opportunities. Our mission is to make it easier for anyone to find, filter and apply to different schools or educational institutions that suit them best as well as make the transition from studies to work more seamless.
We are seeking a detail-oriented QA Tester to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring that all of our software products meet the highest standards of quality and reliability. You will work closely with developers, product managers, and other team members to identify, report, and track bugs and issues. Your main goal will be to ensure that our software products are functional, user-friendly, and meet the needs of our clients.
Salary range will depend on your overall academic qualifications and experience post graduation and will be discussed with you should you be shortlisted for the job.

Job Description
Testing each and every button, page, feature and tool on our platform to verify the functionality and quality of our platform
To create and execute test plans, test cases, and test scripts
Using MS Excel or Google sheets to document each and every step you took to arrive at any results you find and the important things ti note about the result
Documenting any problems, issues and bugs you find that would severely affect the user experience
Using Adobe XD to open prototype designs and analyze the UI/UX
Communicate with team members and stakeholders to provide updates on testing progress and results

Qualifications
A Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology and any related field.
Proven experience as a QA Tester or similar role
Knowledge of software testing methodologies and best practices
Familiarity with bug tracking software
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Ability to work independently and as part of a team
Detail-oriented with a strong focus on quality

Additional Information
Completely remote or work from home (Very good if you also want to spend more time with family)
Friendly and understanding colleagues
You get to work in an agile work environment
You get to show your leadership skills
International working exposure
Company shares can be offered based on how successful with our products' launch
Company sponsored online classes or tech talks
Bonuses if you perform beyond expectation
Promotions towards better job roles possible after a certain period of time

Company Description

SEEKA Technologies (Not Seeka Limited) is a project under its parent organization called Fresh Futures Australia which is an education consultant based in both Australia and Malaysia. We are seeking a detail-oriented QA Tester to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring that all of our software products meet the highest standards of quality and reliability. You will work closely with developers, product managers, and other team members to identify, report, and track bugs and issues. Testing each and every button, page, feature and tool on our platform to verify the functionality and quality of our platform

Using Adobe XD to open prototype designs and analyze the UI/UX
Communicate with team members and stakeholders to provide updates on testing progress and results

A Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology and any related field.

Knowledge of software testing methodologies and best practices
Familiarity with bug tracking software
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Ability to work independently and as part of a team
Detail-oriented with a strong focus on quality

You get to show your leadership skills

About DigitalTolk
DigitalTolk is an organisation and company that works to make an impact. Our purpose is to give a voice to those who don’t speak the local language; we arrange translators so that patients can get medical treatments in their new country and communicate with doctors. We arrange translators for crime victims so that they can get justice. Our job is to arrange interpreters through our platform for our customers.
Our end customers are hospitals, courts/lawyers, and municipalities who communicate with refugees and other people in need.
Our company purpose is to use technology to make the world a better place. And we’re currently hiring developers to join us on this journey!
We are a company based in Sweden with developers in all parts of the planet!

Test automation and test methodology

Experience working with testing APIs
Experience working with automation tests using tools such as Cypress or Selenium.

Experience using project tracking software considered a strong asset (ex: JIRA)

Keen attention to detail

Determination and tenacity to commit to the end when solving issues

Company Description

SEEKA Technologies (Not Seeka Limited) is a project under its parent organization called Fresh Futures Australia which is an education consultant based in both Australia and Malaysia. It will be a huge platform that utilises A.I. to help match students and job seekers to the right opportunities relevant to them from Primary/Grade school to University level as well as language schools and job opportunities. Our mission is to make it easier for anyone to find, filter and apply to different schools or educational institutions that suit them best as well as make the transition from studies to work more seamless.
We are seeking a detail-oriented QA Tester to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring that all of our software products meet the highest standards of quality and reliability. You will work closely with developers, product managers, and other team members to identify, report, and track bugs and issues. Your main goal will be to ensure that our software products are functional, user-friendly, and meet the needs of our clients.
Salary range will depend on your overall academic qualifications and experience post graduation and will be discussed with you should you be shortlisted for the job.

Testing each and every button, page, feature and tool on our platform to verify the functionality and quality of our platform
To create and execute test plans, test cases, and test scripts
Using MS Excel or Google sheets to document each and every step you took to arrive at any results you find and the important things ti note about the result
Documenting any problems, issues and bugs you find that would severely affect the user experience
Using Adobe XD to open prototype designs and analyze the UI/UX
Communicate with team members and stakeholders to provide updates on testing progress and results

A Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology and any related field.

Knowledge of software testing methodologies and best practices
Familiarity with bug tracking software
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Ability to work independently and as part of a team
Detail-oriented with a strong focus on quality

Friendly and understanding colleagues

You get to show your leadership skills
International working exposure
Company shares can be offered based on how successful with our products' launch

Designing and developing AI and ML models: Developing and training machine learning models using Python and ML libraries like TensorFlow, PyTorch, and scikit-learn and working in Image processing.
Data Preprocessing: Preprocessing raw data such as cleaning, filtering, and normalizing data to be used in machine learning algorithms.
Algorithm Development: Developing algorithms for various Machine learning problems such as Classification, Regression, and Clustering.
Identifying and extracting relevant features from raw data that can be used in machine learning algorithms.
Testing and validating the performance of AI and ML models using statistical techniques and measures like cross-validation and confusion matrices.
Deploying and integrating AI and ML models into production environments and maintaining model accuracy.
Collaborating with data scientists, software developers, and business analysts to identify business problems and develop solutions that meet business requirements.
Staying up to date with industry developments: Keeping up-to-date with new machine learning and AI developments and technologies, attending conferences and seminars, and staying abreast of new techniques and algorithms.
Performing other tasks as per the requirements.
Requirements:
Proficiency in programming languages Python and knowledge of machine learning libraries such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, and scikit-learn.
Good knowledge of machine learning algorithms such as supervised learning, unsupervised learning, and reinforcement learning.

Job description
We are looking for an organized, detail-oriented individual to join our team as a software project manager. The responsibilities of the software project manager include overseeing software projects from start to finish, managing and motivating software developers and other team members, giving customer presentations, and writing project proposals.
To be successful as a software project manager, you should have a good working knowledge of project estimation techniques and the ability to motivate team members. Ultimately, a top-notch software project manager should have good communication and decision-making skills.
Software Project Manager Responsibilities:
Discussing potential projects and their parameters with clients, executives, and software developers.
Planning out the blueprints for software projects, including defining the scope, allocating resources, setting deadlines, laying out communication strategies, and indicating tests and maintenance.
Assembling and leading the project team.
Participating in and supervising each stage of the project.
Ensuring each project stays on schedule and adheres to the deadlines.
Creating a project budget and ensuring the project adheres to the budget as closely as possible.
Determining and overseeing consistent testing, evaluation, and troubleshooting of all products in all stages of completion.
Tracking milestones, deliverables, and change requests.
Serving as a liaison to communicate information regarding changes, milestones reached, and other pertinent information.
Delivering completed software products to clients and performing regular checks on the products' performance.
Software Project Manager Requirements:
A bachelor's degree in information technology, software development management, software engineering, computer science, or a related field.
Proven experience in project management and software development.
Good working knowledge of project estimation techniques.
Excellent technical knowledge.
Good leadership, decision-making, and organization skills.
Strong attention to detail and multi-tasking skills.

Job Description:
We are seeking an experienced full-stack developer who is proficient in Python/Django and React.js to join our team. The ideal candidate will have a strong understanding of software architectures, including MVC, MVVM, Clean, MicroServices, etc., and the ability to create GraphQL APIs and optimize ORM queries. Additionally, experience with Google Cloud Platform (GCP) would be a plus.
As a full-stack developer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and deploying applications using Python, Django, and React.js, and creating and maintaining Restful & GraphQL APIs to expose data to various client applications. You will also be responsible for code analysis/review, optimization, and refactoring as necessary, as well as implementing security and data protection measures.
Essential Job Functions:
- Design and develop applications using Python/Django and React.js
- Create Restful APIs and optimize ORM queries
- Develop new and maintain existing features in current applications built with Django & Flask
- Conduct system integration testing procedures, prepare test scripts and data
- Design system enhancement processes, develop materials for end-users, and communicate with the client to gather project requirements
- Collaborate with the team working on different layers of the infrastructure
- Understand business requirements and translate them into technical requirements
- Write well-documented, reusable, and clean code
- Solve complex problems
- Optimize existing code and refactor when necessary
- Ensure application robustness and easy maintenance
- Work in a fast-paced environment
Qualifications Needed:
- 2+ years of professional experience with Python, Flask, Django, Restful APIs, PostgreSQL/MySQL/NoSQL/SQLAlchemy
- Experience with React JS, and Bootstrap
- Proficiency in writing databases ORM queries in an optimized way
- Familiarity with Flask and micro-frameworks
- Strong understanding of OOP and Data Structures
- Ability to understand business requirements and translate them into technical requirements
- Knack for benchmarking and optimization
- Familiarity with code versioning tools, such as Git

Job description
We are looking for an organized, detail-oriented individual to join our team as a software project manager. The responsibilities of the software project manager include overseeing software projects from start to finish, managing and motivating software developers and other team members, giving customer presentations, and writing project proposals.
To be successful as a software project manager, you should have a good working knowledge of project estimation techniques and the ability to motivate team members. Ultimately, a top-notch software project manager should have good communication and decision-making skills.
Software Project Manager Responsibilities:
Discussing potential projects and their parameters with clients, executives, and software developers.
Planning out the blueprints for software projects, including defining the scope, allocating resources, setting deadlines, laying out communication strategies, and indicating tests and maintenance.
Assembling and leading the project team.
Participating in and supervising each stage of the project.
Ensuring each project stays on schedule and adheres to the deadlines.
Creating a project budget and ensuring the project adheres to the budget as closely as possible.
Determining and overseeing consistent testing, evaluation, and troubleshooting of all products in all stages of completion.
Tracking milestones, deliverables, and change requests.
Serving as a liaison to communicate information regarding changes, milestones reached, and other pertinent information.
Delivering completed software products to clients and performing regular checks on the products' performance.
Software Project Manager Requirements:
A bachelor's degree in information technology, software development management, software engineering, computer science, or a related field.
Proven experience in project management and software development.
Good working knowledge of project estimation techniques.
Excellent technical knowledge.
Good leadership, decision-making, and organization skills.
Strong attention to detail and multi-tasking skills.

Salary: Rs250,000.00 - Rs350,000.00 per month

Our mission is to make it easier for anyone to find, filter and apply to different schools or educational institutions that suit them best as well as make the transition from studies to work more seamless.
We are seeking a detail-oriented QA Tester to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring that all of our software products meet the highest standards of quality and reliability. You will work closely with developers, product managers, and other team members to identify, report, and track bugs and issues. Your main goal will be to ensure that our software products are functional, user-friendly, and meet the needs of our clients.
Salary range will depend on your overall academic qualifications and experience post graduation and will be discussed with you should you be shortlisted for the job.

Job Description
Testing each and every button, page, feature and tool on our platform to verify the functionality and quality of our platform
To create and execute test plans, test cases, and test scripts
Using MS Excel or Google sheets to document each and every step you took to arrive at any results you find and the important things ti note about the result
Documenting any problems, issues and bugs you find that would severely affect the user experience
Using Adobe XD to open prototype designs and analyze the UI/UX
Communicate with team members and stakeholders to provide updates on testing progress and results

Qualifications
A Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology and any related field.
Proven experience as a QA Tester or similar role
Knowledge of software testing methodologies and best practices
Familiarity with bug tracking software
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Ability to work independently and as part of a team
Detail-oriented with a strong focus on quality

Additional Information
Completely remote or work from home (Very good if you also want to spend more time with family)
Friendly and understanding colleagues
You get to work in an agile work environment
You get to show your leadership skills
International working exposure
Company shares can be offered based on how successful with our products' launch
Company sponsored online classes or tech talks
Bonuses if you perform beyond expectation
Promotions towards better job roles possible after a certain period of time

- Create Restful APIs and optimize ORM queries
